The paper presents a framework for machine learning that involves multiple agents learning different tasks and/or from different datasets. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). However, given that the paper focuses on learning a global model by aggregating local learnings, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because the paper discusses applications such as image classification (cs.CV) and federated learning (cs.SI).
